Rising act Raymond Fix has announced his single ‘Pere’ will be released on April 1. The single, he said, is a vibrant afrobeat song that merges RnB and afro distinct sounds with the confidence of a danceable tune.   Bruce Willis retires from acting     This cuts deep, 2baba replies wife’s elder brother     You are a bloody liar, Annie Idibia replies elder brother   According to him: “The inspiration draws from a vast range of influences including Afro-pop and alternative afro music.” Speaking on his social media handles @raymondfix on Twitter and Instagram, he said he hopes to leave a lasting impression with listeners of sounds and originality they have never heard before with the first project of the year.